# BSR App - Development Log

## 2026-03-09 - Research & Architecture

### Investigation: bibliothequesonore.ch
- REJECTED: Audio content entirely behind BSR membership auth (visual impairment certification required)
- No public API, no audio samples, no excerpts accessible without login
- Drupal CMS with no exposed REST/JSON endpoints

### Investigation: lausanne.ebibliomedia.ch (Cantook by Demarque)
- SUCCESS: Full OPDS 2.0 API discovered
- Platform: Cantook Station by Demarque (Rails backend)
- 705 audiobooks, 10,440 ebooks in the catalog

### API Endpoints Discovered
- Auth: OAuth 2.0 password grant at `/oauth/token`
- Auth document: `/v1/sign_in.opds2` (OPDS authentication document)
- Search: `/v1/resources.opds2?query={q}` (supports `formats[]=audiobook` filter)
- Book detail: `/resources/{id}.opds2`
- Loans: `/v1/my_profile/activity.opds2`
- History: `/v1/my_profile/history.opds2`
- Wishlist: `/v1/my_profile/wishlist.opds2`
- Progression: `/resources/{id}/progression.opds2` (PUT/GET)
- Profile: `/v1/my_profile.opds2`

### Audio Delivery
- Streaming: Cantooka audio player via signed HTML URLs (`/loans/{id}.html?drm=none&nonce=...&token=...`)
- Cantooka player is a Vue.js SPA that plays Readium WebPub manifests
- Manifests at `edenlivres.fr/audio/{id}/manifest.json` (public = sample only, authenticated = full)
- MP3 files hosted on `assets.edenlivres.fr`
- LCP DRM option also available (`application/audiobook+lcp`)
- Sample MP3s publicly accessible

### Architecture Decisions
1. **Framework**: React Native + Expo (TypeScript) — single codebase, simplest build pipeline
2. **Audio playback**: WebView embedding Cantooka player — leverages existing player (speed control, chapters built-in)
3. **Auth**: OAuth 2.0 password grant via `/oauth/token`
4. **Position tracking**: AsyncStorage locally + server progression API sync
5. **Design**: ebibliomedia palette (Red #CA0000, Green #56AA5E, Orange #AB4200)
6. **Navigation**: expo-router with tabs (Search, Library, Profile) + modal player

### Design Decisions
- Minimal UI: 3 tabs + detail/player screens
- Book cards with cover thumbnails, title, author, duration badge
- Audio-only filter toggle on search
- Loan list with progress bars
- Cantooka WebView for playback (already handles speed, chapters, position)
- Red/white theme matching ebibliomedia branding

## 2026-03-10 - Implementation

### Files Created
- `src/types/index.ts` - TypeScript types (OPDSPublication, Book, Loan, etc.)
- `src/api/client.ts` - Full OPDS API client (auth, search, loans, progression)
- `src/context/auth.tsx` - React auth context with session restore
- `src/theme.ts` - Design tokens (colors, spacing, typography)
- `app/_layout.tsx` - Root layout with auth provider
- `app/index.tsx` - Entry point with auth redirect
- `app/login.tsx` - Login screen (email + password)
- `app/(tabs)/_layout.tsx` - Tab navigator
- `app/(tabs)/index.tsx` - Search screen with debounced input + audio filter
- `app/(tabs)/library.tsx` - Loans list with progress tracking
- `app/(tabs)/settings.tsx` - Profile/logout
- `app/book/[id].tsx` - Book detail with borrow/listen actions
- `app/player/[id].tsx` - WebView Cantooka player with position saving

### Key Technical Notes
- OAuth tokens stored in expo-secure-store (encrypted)
- Position saved every 10s via JS injection into WebView
- Auto token refresh on 401 responses
- Search debounced at 500ms
- WebView communicates position back via postMessage
